President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Allan R. Landon to serve on the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System. Landon has a wealth of experience in the financial industry, particularly as a community banker. He served as Chairman and CEO of Bank of Hawaii Corporation from 2004 to 2010 and has held various positions at Bank of Hawaii and First American Corp. Landon also worked at Ernst & Young LLP. President Obama believes Landon's expertise and knowledge of the financial system will serve the country well during this important time for the economy.